Identify the following rhythm: <image 1>

A. Normal Sinus Rhythm
B. Sinus Tachycardia
C. NSR with PAC'c
D. NSR with 1st Degree AV Block
E. NSR with PVC's
F. Junctional Tachycardia

The rhythm in the image is:

C. NSR with PAC's

This is because the rhythm is normal sinus rhythm (NSR) with premature atrial contractions (PAC's).
